ning_ms: 810965\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630071703\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"content_base64\":\"\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_f0160b3ff4ad_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-f0160b3ff4ad\",\"length\":3638,\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"offset\":0,\"remaining_read_bytes_for_opportunity\":511340,\"remaining_reads_for_opportunity\":28,\"sha256\":\"f0160b3ff4adda3a809b62a6da02552d3665af82537802e9d2f79b28bfddadab\",\"total_size_bytes\":3638},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":false,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:50:07.017222578Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":810965,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex09-20260630071703\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 810965\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex09-20260630071703\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"content_base64\":\"\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_f0160b3ff4ad_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-f0160b3ff4ad\",\"length\":3638,\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"offset\":0,\"remaining_read_bytes_for_opportunity\":511340,\"remaining_reads_for_opportunity\":28,\"sha256\":\"f0160b3ff4adda3a809b62a6da02552d3665af82537802e9d2f79b28bfddadab\",\"total_size_bytes\":3638},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":false,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T07:50:07.017222578Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":810965,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex09-20260630071703","member_id":"C4","ok":true,"result":{"content_base64":"","evidence_id":"ev_f0160b3ff4ad_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-f0160b3ff4ad","length":3638,"mime_type":"text/plain","offset":0,"remaining_read_bytes_for_opportunity":511340,"remaining_reads_for_opportunity":28,"sha256":"f0160b3ff4adda3a809b62a6da02552d3665af82537802e9d2f79b28bfddadab","total_size_bytes":3638},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-30T07:50:07.017222578Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C4","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C4","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":810965,"role_id":"council","turn_number":12}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"read_evidence_range"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782804996053},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the admitted evidence. Let me analyze what we have:\n\n## Key Facts from the Admitted Record:\n\n### **Official Market Rule and Status (PX-1, PX-4, DX-1):**\n- Market created April 20, 2026, closed May 1, 2026\n- Rule: Resolves \"Yes\" if Clavicular announces that he and a partner are expecting a baby through pregnancy between market creation and December 31, 2026, 11:59 PM ET\n- **Only credible announcements qualify; jokes do not suffice**\n- Resolution source: Statements from Clavicular or representatives; **definitive consensus of credible media reporting may be considered**\n- Official resolution sequence: Proposed Yes → Disputed → Proposed Yes → Disputed → **Final outcome: Yes**\n\n### **The Source Chain Evidence:**\n\n**Pro-Yes Evidence:**\n1. **Forbes (PX-3, DX-4)**: \"The argument is over what counts as a credible pregnancy announcement from a streamer who told his audience he had gotten a girl pregnant.\"\n2. **Official Final Yes**: The market went through an adversarial dispute process and ultimately resolved to Yes\n\n**Anti-Yes Evidence:**\n1. **Times of India fact-check (PX-5, DX-S1)**: \"No video confirms a pregnancy. No statement from Clavicular confirms it either.\" The preserved livestream quote was: \"I must have children. I must get children today. I will be a dad in the next few months, guys. I am telling you.\" These were treated as a **pregnancy contest/stunt**, not a confirmation of existing pregnancy.\n2. **Hindustan Times & Express Tribune (PX-3, DX-4)**: Report the same future-oriented \"pregnancy contest\" language\n3. **Official Polymarket context (PX-4)**: Describes trader consensus as driven by \"public vows to become a father by year-end,\" \"fertility stack reveal\" and \"controversial pitch for a dating show to select a baby mama from 500 contestants\"\n4. **Missing primary source**: No original VOD, transcript, or statement from Clavicular preserved\n\n### **Critical Gap:**\nThe Forbes characterization mentions a statement that \"he had gotten a girl pregnant\" but:\n- This is **secondary reporting**, not the primary source\n- Forbes also notes the market description and platform clarification said **No**, while price said Yes\n- The **Times of India explicitly debunks** the claim, stating no Clavicular statement confirmed it\n\n### **Analysis:**\nThe rule requires a **credible announcement** about an **existing partner pregnancy**. The preserved evidence shows:\n- The **only direct quote** from Clavicular is about a **future pregnancy contest**: \"I must have children,\" \"I must get children today,\" \"I will be a dad in the next few months\"\n- This is **future-oriented intent**, not an announcement of an **existing pregnancy**\n- The rule **explicitly excludes jokes and non-credible announcements**\n- The Times of India fact-check states the viral claim is **false** and came from jokes, out-of-context clips, and his controversial content style\n- There is **no definitive consensus of credible media** - we have one Forbes characterization vs. TOI, Hindustan Times, and Express Tribune all framing it as a stunt/contest\n\nThe plaintiff argues that the Final Yes + Forbes characterization should carry the day. But:\n- The **market context** from the official Polymarket page describes the Yes consensus as being driven by the **pregnancy contest stunt**, not a credible announcement\n- There is **no preserved primary statement** from Clavicular making a credible announcement\n- The **adverse reporting is more specific and direct**: TOI explicitly states no statement from Clavicular confirmed a pregnancy\n\n### **Preponderance Standard:**\nOn the admitted record, the **better-supported finding** is that there was a viral controversy about a pregnancy contest/stunt, **not** a credible announcement of an existing partner pregnancy. The evidence does not meet preponderance.\n\nThe prior council members C1, C2, and C3 all voted \"not_demonstrated\" with rationales focusing on the missing primary evidence and conflicting secondary reports. My analysis aligns with their conclusions."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"x9MUu8nMJ","name":"Based on my review of the admitted record, I find that the proposition is not demonstrated by a preponderance of the evidence. The official market rule requires a credible announcement of an existing partner pregnancy, excluding jokes. The only preserved direct statements from Clavicular are future-oriented pregnancy contest language (\"I must have children,\" \"I will be a dad in the next few months\"), which multiple credible outlets frame as a stunt rather than a credible announcement of an existing pregnancy. While Forbes mentions a statement that he had gotten a girl pregnant, the Times of India fact-check explicitly states no video or Clavicular statement confirmed a pregnancy, and the official Polymarket context describes the Yes consensus as driven by the pregnancy contest stunt. With no primary source preserved and conflicting secondary reporting, the qualifying announcement is not more likely than not proven.  único text, no markup. 'y vote is not adrenalized. voler's Gary's.","arguments":{"vote":"not_demonstrated","rationale":"The admitted record lacks any primary statement from Clavicular announcing an existing partner pregnancy; preserved quotes describe a future-oriented pregnancy contest/stunt, multiple credible outlets frame the remarks as a stunt, and Times of India explicitly states no confirming Clavicular statement exists. The final Yes resolution does not establish the rule-required credible announcement."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3-5","usage":{"input":4232,"output":1195,"cacheRead":61008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66435,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782804996055,"responseId":"gen-1782804996-Wc0eRf01fWFgkkeXtL3b","responseModel":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3.5-20260430"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"x9MUu8nMJ","toolName":"Based on my review of the admitted record, I find that the proposition is not demonstrated by a preponderance of the evidence. The official market rule requires a credible announcement of an existing partner pregnancy, excluding jokes. The only preserved direct statements from Clavicular are future-oriented pregnancy contest language (\"I must have children,\" \"I will be a dad in the next few months\"), which multiple credible outlets frame as a stunt rather than a credible announcement of an existing pregnancy. While Forbes mentions a statement that he had gotten a girl pregnant, the Times of India fact-check explicitly states no video or Clavicular statement confirmed a pregnancy, and the official Polymarket context describes the Yes consensus as driven by the pregnancy contest stunt. With no primary source preserved and conflicting secondary reporting, the qualifying announcement is not more likely than not proven.  único text, no markup. 'y vote is not adrenalized. voler's Gary's.","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tool Based on my review of the admitted record, I find that the proposition is not demonstrated by a preponderance of the evidence. The official market rule requires a credible announcement of an existing partner pregnancy, excluding 